{
  "info": {
    "name": "LinkSnip — URL Shortener API",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for testing the URL Shortener REST API.\n\nHow to use:\n1. Import this file into Postman (File → Import)\n2. Set the `baseUrl` variable to your server (default: http://localhost:8080)\n3. Run requests in order: Create → Get Details → Redirect → Delete",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "description": "Change this to your deployed URL in production"
    },
    {
      "key": "shortCode",
      "value": "abc123",
      "description": "Auto-populated after Create Short URL request"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Create Short URL (Auto-generated code)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "// Automatically save the shortCode for use in later requests",
              "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set('shortCode', json.shortCode);",
              "    console.log('Short code saved:', json.shortCode);",
              "}",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status is 201 Created', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response has shortUrl', () => {",
              "    const json = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(json.shortUrl).to.include(pm.collectionVariables.get('baseUrl'));",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Click count starts at 0', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().clickCount).to.eql(0);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"originalUrl\": \"https://www.github.com/yourusername/url-shortener\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "urls"]
        },
        "description": "Creates a short URL with an auto-generated 6-character code.\n\n**Expected Response (201):**\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": 1,\n  \"originalUrl\": \"https://www.github.com/...\",\n  \"shortCode\": \"a8bX2k\",\n  \"shortUrl\": \"http://localhost:8080/a8bX2k\",\n  \"clickCount\": 0,\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00\",\n  \"isActive\": true\n}\n```"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Create Short URL (Custom code)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 201 Created', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Uses our custom code', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().shortCode).to.eql('my-custom-link');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"originalUrl\": \"https://spring.io/projects/spring-boot\",\n  \"customCode\": \"my-custom-link\",\n  \"title\": \"Spring Boot Documentation\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2025-12-31T23:59:59\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "urls"]
        },
        "description": "Creates a short URL with a custom short code, title, and expiration date."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Create Short URL (Validation Error — bad URL)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 400 Bad Request', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(400);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Has fieldErrors object', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('fieldErrors');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"originalUrl\": \"not-a-valid-url\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "urls"]
        },
        "description": "Demonstrates validation error. URL must start with http:// or https://\n\n**Expected Response (400):**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": 400,\n  \"error\": \"Bad Request\",\n  \"message\": \"Validation failed. Check 'fieldErrors' for details.\",\n  \"fieldErrors\": {\n    \"originalUrl\": \"URL must start with http:// or https://\"\n  }\n}\n```"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Create Short URL (Conflict — code already taken)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 409 Conflict', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(409);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"originalUrl\": \"https://www.example.com\",\n  \"customCode\": \"my-custom-link\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "urls"]
        },
        "description": "Try to use a custom code that was already taken in request #2.\n\n**Expected Response (409):**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": 409,\n  \"error\": \"Conflict\",\n  \"message\": \"Short code 'my-custom-link' is already in use.\"\n}\n```"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Get All URLs",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Returns an array', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Array is not empty', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().length).to.be.greaterThan(0);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "urls"]
        },
        "description": "Returns a list of all shortened URL mappings.\n\n**Expected Response (200):**\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"shortCode\": \"a8bX2k\",\n    \"originalUrl\": \"https://github.com/...\",\n    \"shortUrl\": \"http://localhost:8080/a8bX2k\",\n    \"clickCount\": 0,\n    ...\n  }\n]\n```"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Get URL Details by Short Code",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Short code matches', () => {",
              "    const code = pm.collectionVariables.get('shortCode');",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().shortCode).to.eql(code);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls/{{shortCode}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "urls", "{{shortCode}}"]
        },
        "description": "Get details and statistics for a specific short URL.\nUses the `shortCode` variable auto-populated from request #1."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "7. Get URL Details — 404 Not Found",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 404 Not Found', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(404);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Error message mentions the code', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('doesnotexist');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls/doesnotexist",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "urls", "doesnotexist"]
        },
        "description": "Demonstrates 404 response for non-existent short code.\n\n**Expected Response (404):**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": 404,\n  \"error\": \"Not Found\",\n  \"message\": \"Short URL 'doesnotexist' not found.\"\n}\n```"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "8. Redirect (Follow redirect to original URL)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "// Note: Postman follows redirects automatically by default.",
              "// To see the raw 302, disable 'Follow Redirects' in Postman settings.",
              "pm.test('Request succeeded (redirect followed)', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/{{shortCode}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["{{shortCode}}"]
        },
        "description": "Redirects to the original URL.\n\n**Raw Response (302) — disable redirect following to see this:**\n```\nHTTP/1.1 302 Found\nLocation: https://www.github.com/yourusername/url-shortener\n```\n\nAfter this request, the click count for the URL should be incremented by 1."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "9. Deactivate URL",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 204 No Content', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(204);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response body is empty', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.be.empty;",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "DELETE",
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/urls/{{shortCode}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "urls", "{{shortCode}}"]
        },
        "description": "Soft-deletes a short URL (sets isActive = false).\nThe record is kept in the database but the redirect no longer works.\n\n**Expected Response: 204 No Content (empty body)**"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "10. Verify Deactivated URL Returns 404",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 404 (deactivated URLs not found)', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(404);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/{{shortCode}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["{{shortCode}}"]
        },
        "description": "After deactivation, visiting the short URL should return 404.\nThis verifies the soft-delete worked correctly."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "11. Health Check",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('App status is UP', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('UP');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/health",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["actuator", "health"]
        },
        "description": "Spring Boot Actuator health endpoint.\nUseful for deployment health checks.\n\n**Expected Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"UP\",\n  \"components\": {\n    \"db\": { \"status\": \"UP\" },\n    \"diskSpace\": { \"status\": \"UP\" }\n  }\n}\n```"
      }
    }
  ]
}
